sentences: Brigitte Engerer (French: [ɑ̃ɡəʁɛʁ]; 27 October 1952 – 23 June 2012) was a French pianist.
In 1968, aged 15, she was unanimously awarded a first prize in piano, and the following year she won the Concours International Marguerite Long-Jacques Thibaud.
Though her scholarship was originally for one year, she loved Russia so much that she studied there for nine years.
Her last concert took place on 12 June 2012 at the prestigious Théâtre des Champs-Elysées, 50 years after playing there for the first time.
She died less than two weeks later, on 23 June, after a several year struggle against cancer.
